{
  "document_id": "sir-24",
  "title": "Sirach 24",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Wisdom praises herself"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "In the assembly of the Most High she opens her mouth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "“I came forth from the mouth of the Most High"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "I encamped in the heights,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Alone I compassed the vault of heaven"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Over waves of the sea, over all the earth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Among all these I sought a resting place;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "“Then the Creator of all things gave me a command,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "Before the ages, in the beginning, he created me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "In the holy tent I ministered before him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Thus in the beloved city he gave me a resting place,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "I took root in an honored people;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "“I grew tall like a cedar in Lebanon"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "I grew tall like a palm tree in En-gedi"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Like cassia and camel’s thorn I gave forth perfume,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Like a terebinth I spread out my branches,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Like the vine I bud forth delights,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "“Come to me, you who desire me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "For the memory of me is sweeter than honey"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Those who eat of me will hunger for more,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Whoever obeys me will not be put to shame,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "All this is the book of the covenant of the Most High God,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "It becomes full, like the Pishon, with wisdom"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "It fills up, like the Euphrates, with understanding,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "It pours forth instruction like the Nile,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "The first man did not know wisdom fully,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "For her thoughts are more abundant than the sea"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "I came forth like a canal from a river,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "I said, “I will water my garden"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "I will again make instruction shine forth like the dawn,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "I will again pour out teaching like prophecy"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "sir-24-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "Observe that I have not labored for myself alone"
    }
  ]
}